President Biden has announced the appointment of Christian L. Tom as Assistant to the President and Director of the Office of Digital Strategy. President Biden praised Tom as an innovator who played a key role in developing a digital strategy for the administration in 2020. Tom's experience in technology, digital media, and social platforms will be utilized to strengthen democracy and bring people together. Additionally, Patrick Stevenson will serve as Deputy Assistant to the President and Senior Advisor for Digital Strategy, while Tericka Lambert will be promoted to Deputy Assistant to the President and Deputy Director of Digital Strategy.